DpWh0HrA==\\\",\\\"summary\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Checking Checkstyle issues**\\\\n\\\\nI need to check a possible issue with Checkstyle about whether a public nested class constructor should indeed be public. The existing constructor is package-private, which seems fine, but there are dynamic-access rules to consider. The user only asks about modifying one file, so I might just add a helper public class that's inner. \\\\n\\\\nThere's also a thought about whether we can strengthen the test to include locale features, but I’m hesitant to add too much complexity. The current test uses a custom resolver already.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering API concerns**\\\\n\\\\nI need to avoid using deprecated APIs, and there's a potential issue with `MethodExpression.isParametersProvided` being misspelled. It's important not to introduce new deprecated elements. I’m thinking about whether we need to use direct reflection, especially since the custom ELResolver may have a package-private constructor. \\\\n\\\\nThere’s also a concern regarding how `getType` in `RootObjectELResolver` returns `Object.class`, which might coerce types unexpectedly. There are a few other conditions to analyze, but overall, I’m not sure we need to add comments to the code. Summarizing the existing test coverage should be enough.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Implemented a new test in:\\n\\n`tests/src/org.glassfish.web/javax.el/2.2.4/src/test/java/org_glassfish_web/javax_el/Javax_elTest.java`\\n\\nWhat existing coverage already included:\\n- ExpressionFactory arithmetic, composite expressions, functions, and variables\\n- Conditional/logical/empty operators\\n- Nested collection read/write and `ValueReference`\\n- Method expressions and method metadata\\n- Standard resolvers for maps, lists, arrays, resource bundles, and beans\\n- Composite resolver ordering\\n- Type coercion and literal value expressions\\n\\nNew feature covered:\\n- Resolution of top-level implicit/root objects through a custom public `ELResolver`, including:\\n  - Reading an implicit object without using `VariableMapper`\\n  - Navigating into that object via `MapELResolver`\\n  - Writing nested values\\n  - Writing top-level root values through the resolver\\n\\nNo existing test logic was changed. I did not run tests, per instruction.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_09d7fa4b6dcb3b3a0169f788c6b71c819796f14ed5a4b75d0a\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1438, \"output\": 641, \"cacheRead\": 17408, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 19487, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1777830075793, \"responseId\": \"resp_09d7fa4b6dcb3b3a0169f788bc41a0819783551b50e5378eca\"}, \"toolResults\": []}\n[recv] agent_end\n[send] get_state\n[recv] get_state success\n  sessionFile: ../../../../../../../../.pi/agent/sessions/--home-vjovanov-c-forge-forge9-graalvm-reachability-metadata-forge-local_repositories-forge_worktrees-3713-1ddb480b--/2026-05-03T17-40-10-230Z_019deeed-1d76-724e-a618-738ecaf7442f.jsonl\n  sessionId: 019deeed-1d76-724e-a618-738ecaf7442f\n[send] get_session_stats\n[recv] get_session_stats success\n  tokens: input=17047 output=5274 cacheRead=152576 cacheWrite=0 total=174897\n\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
